A: Your code is almost correct, but you are not appending the modified lines to the output file. You are just overwriting it each time in the while loop. You should open the PrintWriter outside the while loop and append to it in each iteration. Here is the corrected code:
public class Writefile {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
        try {
            Scanner file = new Scanner(new File("testfile.txt"));
            File output = new File("mdemarco.txt");
            PrintWriter printer = new PrintWriter(output);
            String s = "";
            int n = 0;
            while (file.hasNext()) {
                s = file.nextLine();
                n++;
                System.out.println(n + ". " + s);
                printer.println(n + ". " + s); // append to the file
            }
            printer.close();
        } catch (FileNotFoundException fnfe) {
            System.out.println("Was not able to locate testfile.txt.");
        }
    }
}

This code will append each line of the input file with its line number to the output file.

